    • buttons

      protected javafx.beans.property.ListProperty<ImageButton> buttons()

      Returns the ListProperty containing the buttons in this ImageButtonGroup.

      1. The list returned by this method is not a copy
      2. All changes made to the list returned by this method will be reflected in this ImageButtonGroup.
      Returns:
      The ListProperty containing the buttons in this ImageButtonGroup.

    • getSelectedButton

      public ImageButton getSelectedButton()

      Returns the selected button in this ImageButtonGroup.

      1. getSelectedButton() is identical to selectedButtonProperty().get().
      Returns:
      The selected button in this ImageButtonGroup.
      See Also:

    • isButtonSelected

      public boolean isButtonSelected​(ImageButton button)

      Checks if the specified ImageButton is selected.

      1. If the specified ImageButton is null, this method returns false.
      Parameters:
      button - The ImageButton being checked.
      Returns:
      True if the specified ImageButton is selected, false otherwise.
      See Also:
      selectedButtonProperty(), getSelectedButton(), setSelectedButton(ImageButton)

    • setSelectedButton

      public ImageButton setSelectedButton​(ImageButton button)

      Sets the selected button to the specified value.

      Parameters:
      button - The ImageButton to be selected.
      Returns:
      The previously selected button.
      If no button was selected, this method returns null.
      See Also:
      selectedButtonProperty(), getSelectedButton(), isButtonSelected(ImageButton)

    • clearSelection

      public boolean clearSelection​(ImageButton... buttons)

      If the selected button equals any of the specified values, the selected button is cleared.

      1. If the specified ImageButton array is null, a NullPointerException is thrown.
      2. If the specified ImageButton array is empty, the selected button is always cleared.
      3. Clearing the selected button is identical to setSelectedButton(null).
      Parameters:
      buttons - The array of buttons to be compared for clearing.
      Returns:
      True if the selection was successfully cleared, false if it was not.
      See Also:
      selectedButtonProperty(), getSelectedButton(), setSelectedButton(ImageButton)

    • selectFirst

      public ImageButton selectFirst()

      Selects the first button in this ImageButtonGroup, then returns the previous selection.

      1. If there are no buttons in this ImageButtonGroup, return null.
      Returns:
      The previously selected button, or null if there are no buttons in this ImageButtonGroup.
      See Also:
      selectLast(), selectedButtonProperty(), getSelectedButton(), setSelectedButton(ImageButton)

    • selectLast

      public ImageButton selectLast()

      Selects the last button in this ImageButtonGroup, then returns the previous selection.

      1. If there are no buttons in this ImageButtonGroup, return null.
      Returns:
      The previously selected button, or null if there are no buttons in this ImageButtonGroup.
      See Also:
      selectFirst(), selectedButtonProperty(), getSelectedButton(), setSelectedButton(ImageButton)
